readiness.insight: Based on your VO2 Max of 33.4 ml/kg/min and a sedentary activity level, you have a moderate level of cardiovascular fitness. However, your low step count and lack of regular exercise suggest limited physical activity intensity. Freel Peak, with a difficulty rating of 72 out of 100, requires significant endurance and strength. To improve your readiness, consider incorporating regular walking or jogging into your routine, aiming for at least 30 minutes most days. Gradually increase your distance and intensity to build stamina. Complement this with strength training exercises targeting your legs and core to enhance your climbing ability. Additionally, monitor your progress and adjust your training regimen as needed to prepare adequately for the challenging climb.
